    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. can you add a bit more detail on why this concept is so important for protecting people from state overreach? like, why is it better for protecting rights than just sticking to \"procedural\" due process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is vital because it goes beyond just following procedures; it protects fundamental rights from government overreach. Unlike procedural due process, which focuses on fair procedures, substantive due process ensures that the government can't infringe on essential freedoms like privacy, speech, and equality. This principle has been crucial in landmark cases like Roe v. Wade and Obergefell v. Hodges, which expanded civil rights and protected individual liberties. By safeguarding these freedoms, substantive due process prevents the government from imposing unjust laws and policies, ensuring a more just and equal society. It's a powerful tool for protecting people from state overreach and promoting individual freedoms.",
      "source": "target",
